[Problem 1] Find if two strings are equal or not using Hashing

You are given two strings of size n106n \le 10^6n106. Find if they are equal or not using Hashing.

#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

const int p = 137, mod = 1e9 + 7;

const int N = 1e5 + 9;

int pw[N];
void prec() {
  pw[0] = 1;
  for (int i = 1; i < N; i++) {
    pw[i] = 1LL * pw[i - 1] * p % mod;
  }
}
int get_hash(string s) {
  int n = s.size();
  int hs = 0;
  for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
    hs += 1LL * s[i] * pw[i] % mod;
    hs %= mod;
  }
  return hs;
}
int32_t main() {
  ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  cin.tie(0);
  prec();
  string a, b; cin >> a >> b;
  cout << (get_hash(a) == get_hash(b)) << '\n';
  return 0;
}

Double Hashing

Use two different primes and mods to decrease the probability of collisions. Check this.

#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

const int p1 = 137, mod1 = 1e9 + 7, p2 = 277, mod2 = 1e9 + 9;

const int N = 1e5 + 9;

int pw1[N], pw2[N];
void prec() {
  pw1[0] = 1;
  for (int i = 1; i < N; i++) {
    pw1[i] = 1LL * pw1[i - 1] * p1 % mod1;
  }
  pw2[0] = 1;
  for (int i = 1; i < N; i++) {
    pw2[i] = 1LL * pw2[i - 1] * p2 % mod2;
  }
}
pair<int, int> get_hash(string s) {
  int n = s.size();
  int hs1 = 0;
  for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
    hs1 += 1LL * s[i] * pw1[i] % mod1;
    hs1 %= mod1;
  }  
  int hs2 = 0;
  for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
    hs2 += 1LL * s[i] * pw2[i] % mod2;
    hs2 %= mod2;
  }
  return {hs1, hs2};
}
int32_t main() {
  ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  cin.tie(0);
  prec();
  string a, b; cin >> a >> b;
  cout << (get_hash(a) == get_hash(b)) << '\n';
  return 0;
}

[Problem 3]Pattern Matching

You are given a string sss and another string aaa. Find all occurrences of the string aaa in sss. The lengths of the strings are 106\le 10^6106.

Solve this: link

#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

const int N = 1e6 + 9;
const int p1 = 137, mod1 = 1e9 + 7, p2 = 277, mod2 = 1e9 + 9;


int power(long long n, long long k, int mod) {
  int ans = 1 % mod; n %= mod; if (n < 0) n += mod;
  while (k) {
    if (k & 1) ans = (long long) ans * n % mod;
    n = (long long) n * n % mod;
    k >>= 1;
  }
  return ans;
}

int ip1, ip2;
pair<int, int> pw[N], ipw[N];
void prec() {
  pw[0] =  {1, 1};
  for (int i = 1; i < N; i++) {
    pw[i].first = 1LL * pw[i - 1].first * p1 % mod1;
    pw[i].second = 1LL * pw[i - 1].second * p2 % mod2;
  }
  ip1 = power(p1, mod1 - 2, mod1);
  ip2 = power(p2, mod2 - 2, mod2);
  ipw[0] =  {1, 1};
  for (int i = 1; i < N; i++) {
    ipw[i].first = 1LL * ipw[i - 1].first * ip1 % mod1;
    ipw[i].second = 1LL * ipw[i - 1].second * ip2 % mod2;
  }
}

pair<int, int> string_hash(string s) {
  int n = s.size();
  pair<int, int> hs({0, 0});
  for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
    hs.first += 1LL * s[i] * pw[i].first % mod1;
    hs.first %= mod1;    
    hs.second += 1LL * s[i] * pw[i].second % mod2;
    hs.second %= mod2;
  }
  return hs;
}
pair<int, int> pref[N];
void build(string s) {
  int n = s.size();
  for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
    pref[i].first = 1LL * s[i] * pw[i].first % mod1;
    if (i) pref[i].first = (pref[i].first + pref[i - 1].first) % mod1;
    pref[i].second = 1LL * s[i] * pw[i].second % mod2;
    if (i) pref[i].second = (pref[i].second + pref[i - 1].second) % mod2;
  }
}
pair<int, int> get_hash(int i, int j) {
  assert(i <= j);
  pair<int, int> hs({0, 0});
  hs.first = pref[j].first;
  if (i) hs.first = (hs.first - pref[i - 1].first + mod1) % mod1;
  hs.first = 1LL * hs.first * ipw[i].first % mod1;
  hs.second = pref[j].second;
  if (i) hs.second = (hs.second - pref[i - 1].second + mod2) % mod2;
  hs.second = 1LL * hs.second * ipw[i].second % mod2;
  return hs;
}

int32_t main() {
  ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  cin.tie(0);
  prec();
  string a, b; cin >> a >> b;
  build(a);
  int ans = 0, n = a.size(), m = b.size();
  auto hash_b = string_hash(b);
  for (int i = 0; i + m - 1 < n; i++) {
    ans += get_hash(i, i + m - 1) == hash_b;
  }
  cout << ans << '\n';
  return 0;
}

[Problem 4] Number of Divisors of a String

Given a string sss of size n105n \le 10^5n105. Find the number of divisors of sss. A string bbb is a divisor of sss if it is possible to glue bbb zero or more times to get the string sss. For example, the divisors of abababab are ab, abab and abababab.

Can you solve it in 2s?.

#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

int32_t main() {
  ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  cin.tie(0);
  string s; cin >> s;
  int ans = 0;
  int n = s.size();
  for (int len = 1; len <= n / 2; len++) {
    bool ok = true;
    for (int i = 0; i + len - 1 < n; i += len) {
      ok &= get_hash(i, i + len - 1) == get_hash(0, len - 1);
    }
    ans += ok;
  }
  return 0;
}

[Problem 6] Queries to find the LCP of two substrings

Given a string sss of size nnn and qqq queries of type i,j,x,yi, j, x, yi,j,x,y. Find the LCP of substrings s[ij]s[i \ldots j]s[ij] and s[xy]s[x \ldots y]s[xy]. 1n,q1051 \le n, q \le 10^51n,q105.

int lcp(int i, int j, int x, int y) { // O(log n)
  int l = 1, r = min(j - i + 1, y - x + 1), ans = 0;
  while (l <= r) {
    int mid = l + r >> 1;
    if (get_hash(i, i + mid - 1) == get_hash(x, x + mid - 1)) {
      ans = mid;
      l = mid + 1;
    }
    else {
      r = mid - 1;
    }
  }
  return ans;
}

[Fun Problem]Find if any substring that occurs more than k times

You are given a string sss of size 105\le 10^5105. Find if there exists a string which occurs more than kkk times in sss. Output YES or NO.

[More Fun]Find the largest substring that occurs more than k times

int n;
int max_oc(int len) {
  map<pair<int, int>, int> mp;
  for (int i = 0; i + len - 1 < n; i++) {
    mp[get_hash(i, i + len - 1)]++;
  }
  int ans = 0;
  for (auto [x, y]: mp) {
    ans = max(ans, y);
  }
  return ans;
}
int32_t main() {
  ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  cin.tie(0);
  prec();
  string s; cin >> s;
  build(s);
  int k; cin >> k;
  n = s.size();
  int l = 1, r = s.size(), ans = -1;
  while (l <= r) {
    int mid = (l + r) >> 1;
    if (max_oc(mid) >= k) {
      ans = mid;
      l = mid + 1;
    }
    else {
      r = mid - 1;
    }
  }
  cout << ans << '\n';
  return 0;
}

[Problem 8] Find the Lexicographically Minimal Cyclic Shift of a String

For a given string of length n105n \le 10^5n105, we need to find among all possible cyclic shifts of the string one that goes first in alphabetical order.

#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

const int N = 2e6 + 9;
const int p1 = 137, mod1 = 1e9 + 7, p2 = 277, mod2 = 1e9 + 9;


int power(long long n, long long k, int mod) {
  int ans = 1 % mod; n %= mod; if (n < 0) n += mod;
  while (k) {
    if (k & 1) ans = (long long) ans * n % mod;
    n = (long long) n * n % mod;
    k >>= 1;
  }
  return ans;
}

int ip1, ip2;
pair<int, int> pw[N], ipw[N];
void prec() {
  pw[0] =  {1, 1};
  for (int i = 1; i < N; i++) {
    pw[i].first = 1LL * pw[i - 1].first * p1 % mod1;
    pw[i].second = 1LL * pw[i - 1].second * p2 % mod2;
  }
  ip1 = power(p1, mod1 - 2, mod1);
  ip2 = power(p2, mod2 - 2, mod2);
  ipw[0] =  {1, 1};
  for (int i = 1; i < N; i++) {
    ipw[i].first = 1LL * ipw[i - 1].first * ip1 % mod1;
    ipw[i].second = 1LL * ipw[i - 1].second * ip2 % mod2;
  }
}

pair<int, int> string_hash(string s) {
  int n = s.size();
  pair<int, int> hs({0, 0});
  for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
    hs.first += 1LL * s[i] * pw[i].first % mod1;
    hs.first %= mod1;    
    hs.second += 1LL * s[i] * pw[i].second % mod2;
    hs.second %= mod2;
  }
  return hs;
}
pair<int, int> pref[N];
void build(string s) {
  int n = s.size();
  for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
    pref[i].first = 1LL * s[i] * pw[i].first % mod1;
    if (i) pref[i].first = (pref[i].first + pref[i - 1].first) % mod1;
    pref[i].second = 1LL * s[i] * pw[i].second % mod2;
    if (i) pref[i].second = (pref[i].second + pref[i - 1].second) % mod2;
  }
}
pair<int, int> get_hash(int i, int j) {
  assert(i <= j);
  pair<int, int> hs({0, 0});
  hs.first = pref[j].first;
  if (i) hs.first = (hs.first - pref[i - 1].first + mod1) % mod1;
  hs.first = 1LL * hs.first * ipw[i].first % mod1;
  hs.second = pref[j].second;
  if (i) hs.second = (hs.second - pref[i - 1].second + mod2) % mod2;
  hs.second = 1LL * hs.second * ipw[i].second % mod2;
  return hs;
}
int lcp(int i, int j, int x, int y) { // O(log n)
  int l = 1, r = min(j - i + 1, y - x + 1), ans = 0;
  while (l <= r) {
    int mid = l + r >> 1;
    if (get_hash(i, i + mid - 1) == get_hash(x, x + mid - 1)) {
      ans = mid;
      l = mid + 1;
    }
    else {
      r = mid - 1;
    }
  }
  return ans;
}
/*
0 = equal
-1 = first one is smaller
1 = first one is larger
*/
string s;
int compare(int i, int j, int x, int y) { // O(log n)
  int lc = lcp(i, j, x, y);
  int len1 = j - i + 1, len2 = y - x + 1;
  if (len1 == len2 and lc == len1) return 0; //equal
  else if (lc == len1) return -1;
  else if (lc == len2) return 1;
  else return (s[i + lc] < s[x + lc] ? -1 : 1);
}
int32_t main() {
  ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  cin.tie(0);
  cin >> s;
  int n = s.size();
  s += s;
  prec();
  build(s);
  int mni = 0, mnj = n - 1;
  for (int i = 1; i < n; i++) {
    int x = compare(mni, mnj, i, i + n - 1);
    if (x == 1) {
      mni = i, mnj = i + n - 1;
    }
  }
  cout << s.substr(mni, n) << '\n';
  return 0;
}

[Complexity Check] Try this

Say we have n105n \le 10^5n105 strings and the sum of the sizes of the strings is s=3105\le s = 3 \cdot 10^5s=3105. If we insert the strings one my one in a map, what will be the time complexity?

Solution $O(s \log n)$ because each time we insert a string of size $l$, then it will take $O(l \log n)$ time. Note that when we compare two strings of sizes $x$ and $y$, it takes $O(\min(x, y))$ time.

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

bool is_pal(string& s) {
    for(int i = 0; i < s.size(); i++) {
        if(s[i] != s[s.size() - i - 1]) return false;
    }
    return true;
}

int32_t main() {
    ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0); cin.tie(0);
    int t;
    cin >> t;
    while(t--) {
        string s;
        cin >> s;
        sort(s.begin(), s.end());
        if(is_pal(s)) cout << -1 << '\n';
        else cout << s << '\n';
    }
return 0;
}

int32_t main() {
    ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0); cin.tie(0);
    string s;
    cin >> s;
    stack<char> stk;
    bool win = 0;
    for(int i = 0; i < s.size(); i++) {
        if(!stk.empty() && stk.top() == s[i]) {
            win ^= 1;
            stk.pop();
        }
        else {
            stk.push(s[i]);
        }
    }
    cout << (win ? "Yes" : "No") << '\n';

}

char change(char a, char b, int c) {
    if(((c + 1 - 'a') % 26) != b - 'a') return ((c + 1 - 'a') % 26) + 'a';

4. Problem D

Editorial: N/A

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

const int N = 1e3 + 9;

int modpow(long long a, long long n, const int m) {
    int r = 1 % m;
    a %= m;
    if(n < 0) a += m;
    while (n) {
        if(n & 1) r = (long long) r * a % m;
        a = (long long) a * a % m;
        n >>= 1;
    }
    return r;
}

const int MOD1 = 127657753, MOD2 = 987654319;
const int p1 = 137, p2 = 277;
int ip1, ip2;
pair<int, int> pw[N], ipw[N];
void prec() {
    pw[0] = {1, 1};
    for(int i = 1; i < N; i++) {
        pw[i].first = 1LL * pw[i - 1].first * p1 % MOD1;
        pw[i].second = 1LL * pw[i - 1].second * p2 % MOD2;
    }
    ip1 = modpow(p1, MOD1 - 2, MOD1);
    ip2 = modpow(p2, MOD2 - 2, MOD2);
    ipw[0] = {1, 1};
    for(int i = 1; i < N; i++) {
        ipw[i].first = 1LL * ipw[i - 1].first * ip1 % MOD1;
        ipw[i].second = 1LL * ipw[i - 1].second * ip2 % MOD2;
    }
}
struct Hashing {
    int n;
    string s;
    vector<pair<int, int>> hs;
    Hashing() {}
    Hashing(string _s) {
        n = _s.size();
        s = _s;
        hs.emplace_back(0, 0);
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            pair<int, int> p;
            p.first = (hs[i].first + 1LL * pw[i].first * s[i] % MOD1) % MOD1;
            p.second = (hs[i].second + 1LL * pw[i].second * s[i] % MOD2) % MOD2;
            hs.push_back(p);
        }
    }
    pair<int, int> get_hash(int l, int r) {
        assert(1 <= l && l <= r && r <= n);
        pair<int, int> ans;
        ans.first = (hs[r].first - hs[l - 1].first + MOD1) * 1LL * ipw[l - 1].first % MOD1;
        ans.second = (hs[r].second - hs[l - 1].second + MOD2) * 1LL * ipw[l - 1].second % MOD2;
        return ans;
    }
    pair<int, int> get_hash() {
        return get_hash(1, n);
    }
}hs, hrs;

int lcp(Hashing& ha, Hashing& hb, int ai = -1, int aj = -1, int bi = -1, int bj = -1) {
    if(ai == -1) {
        ai = 0, aj = ha.n - 1, bi = 0, bj = hb.n - 1;
    }
    int l = 1, r = min(aj - ai + 1, bj - bi + 1), m;
    int ans = 0;
    while(l <= r) {
        m = l + r >> 1;
        if(ha.get_hash(ai, ai + m - 1) == hb.get_hash(bi, bi + m - 1)) {
            ans = m;
            l = m + 1;
        }
        else {
            r = m - 1;
        }
    }
    return ans;
}

bool compare(Hashing& ha, Hashing& hb, int i, int j, int x, int y) {
    int lc = lcp(ha, hb, i, j, x, y);
    int l1 = (j - i + 1), l2 = (y - x + 1);
    if(lc == l1 or lc == l2) {
        return l1 <= l2;
    }
    return ha.s[i + lc - 1] < hb.s[x + lc - 1];
}

int n;

int ispalindrome(int i, int j) {
    return hs.get_hash(i, j) == hrs.get_hash(n - j + 1, n - i + 1);
}

int32_t main() {
    ios_base::sync_with_stdio(false); cin.tie(NULL);
    prec();

    string s;
    while(cin >> s) {
        n = (int)s.size();
        hs = Hashing(s);
        reverse(s.begin(), s.end());
        hrs = Hashing(s);
        reverse(s.begin(), s.end());
        auto cmp = [&](pair<int, int> x, pair<int, int> y) {
            return compare(hs, hs, x.first, x.second, y.first, y.second);
        };
        vector<pair<int, int>> palpairs;
        set<pair<int, int>> taken;
        for(int i = 0; i < hs.n; i++) {
            for(int j = i + 1; j < hs.n; j++) {
                if(ispalindrome(i + 1, j + 1) and taken.count(hs.get_hash(i + 1, j + 1)) == 0) {
                    taken.insert(hs.get_hash(i + 1, j + 1));
                    palpairs.push_back({i + 1, j + 1});
                }
            }
        }
        sort(palpairs.begin(), palpairs.end(), cmp);
        for(auto x: palpairs) {
            cout << s.substr(x.first - 1, x.second - x.first + 1) << '\n';
        }
        cout << '\n';
    }

return 0;
}

        }

    string s;

    int n = (int)s.size();
    int zer = 0, one = 0;
    for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        if(s[i] == '1') one++;
    }
    zer = n - one;

                        nope = true;
                        break;

                    if(ohash == zhash) {
                        nope = true;
                        break;
                    }
                }
                j += y;
            }
        }
        if(!nope) {
            ans++;
        }
    }
    cout << ans << '\n';

}

        G[x].push_back(y);
        G[y].push_back(x);
        GG[x].push_back(y);
        GG[y].push_back(x);
    }
    for(int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
        sort(G[i].begin(), G[i].end());
    }
    sort(G + 1, G + n + 1);
    long long ans = 0;
    int cnt = 1;
    for(int i = 2; i <= n; i++) {
        if(G[i] == G[i - 1]) cnt++;
        else {
            ans += (1LL * cnt * (cnt - 1)) / 2;
            cnt = 1;
        }
    }
    ans += (1LL * cnt * (cnt - 1)) / 2;
    for(int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
        GG[i].push_back(i);
    }
    for(int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
        sort(GG[i].begin(), GG[i].end());
    }
    sort(GG + 1, GG + n + 1);
    cnt = 1;
    for(int i = 2; i <= n; i++) {
        if(GG[i] == GG[i - 1]) cnt++;
        else {
            ans += (1LL * cnt * (cnt - 1)) / 2;
            cnt = 1;
        }
    }
    ans += (1LL * cnt * (cnt - 1)) / 2;
    cout << ans << '\n';

return 0;
}

Timus 1517: Freedom of Choice

Editorial: N/A

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

const int N = 1e6 + 9;

int modpow(long long a, long long n, const int m) {
    int r = 1 % m;
    a %= m;
    if(n < 0) a += m;
    while (n) {
        if(n & 1) r = (long long) r * a % m;
        a = (long long) a * a % m;
        n >>= 1;
    }
    return r;
}

const int MOD1 = 127657753, MOD2 = 987654319;
const int p1 = 137, p2 = 277;
int ip1, ip2;
pair<int, int> pw[N], ipw[N];
void prec() {
    pw[0] = {1, 1};
    for(int i = 1; i < N; i++) {
        pw[i].first = 1LL * pw[i - 1].first * p1 % MOD1;
        pw[i].second = 1LL * pw[i - 1].second * p2 % MOD2;
    }
    ip1 = modpow(p1, MOD1 - 2, MOD1);
    ip2 = modpow(p2, MOD2 - 2, MOD2);
    ipw[0] = {1, 1};
    for(int i = 1; i < N; i++) {
        ipw[i].first = 1LL * ipw[i - 1].first * ip1 % MOD1;
        ipw[i].second = 1LL * ipw[i - 1].second * ip2 % MOD2;
    }
}
struct Hashing {
    int n;
    string s;
    vector<pair<int, int>> hs;
    Hashing() {}
    Hashing(string _s) {
        n = _s.size();
        s = _s;
        hs.emplace_back(0, 0);
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            pair<int, int> p;
            p.first = (hs[i].first + 1LL * pw[i].first * s[i] % MOD1) % MOD1;
            p.second = (hs[i].second + 1LL * pw[i].second * s[i] % MOD2) % MOD2;
            hs.push_back(p);
        }
    }
    pair<int, int> get_hash(int l, int r) {
        assert(1 <= l && l <= r && r <= n);
        pair<int, int> ans;
        ans.first = (hs[r].first - hs[l - 1].first + MOD1) * 1LL * ipw[l - 1].first % MOD1;
        ans.second = (hs[r].second - hs[l - 1].second + MOD2) * 1LL * ipw[l - 1].second % MOD2;
        return ans;
    }
    pair<int, int> get_hash() {
        return get_hash(1, n);
    }
};

int lcp(Hashing& ha, Hashing& hb, int ai = -1, int aj = -1, int bi = -1, int bj = -1) {
    if(ai == -1) {
        ai = 0, aj = ha.n - 1, bi = 0, bj = hb.n - 1;
    }
    ai += 1, aj += 1, bi += 1, bj += 1;
    int l = 1, r = min(aj - ai + 1, bj - bi + 1), m;
    int ans = 0;
    while(l <= r) {
        m = l + r >> 1;
        if(ha.get_hash(ai, ai + m - 1) == hb.get_hash(bi, bi + m - 1)) {
            ans = m;
            l = m + 1;
        }
        else {
            r = m - 1;
        }
    }
    return ans;
}

int okay(Hashing& ha, Hashing& hb, int l) {
    set<pair<int, int>> st;
    for(int i = 1; i + l - 1 <= ha.n; i++) {
        st.insert(ha.get_hash(i, i + l - 1));
    }
    for(int i = 1; i + l - 1 <= hb.n; i++) {
        if(st.count(hb.get_hash(i, i + l - 1))) return i;
    }
    return -1;
}

int32_t main() {
    ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0); cin.tie(0);
    prec();
    
    int n;
    cin >> n;
    string sa, sb;
    cin >> sa >> sb;
    Hashing ha(sa), hb(sb);

    int l = 1, r = n;
    pair<int, int> ans = {0, -1};
    while(l <= r) {
        int m = l + r >> 1;
        int ok = okay(ha, hb, m);
        if(ok != -1) {
            ans = {m, ok};
            l = m + 1;
        }
        else {
            r = m - 1;
        }
    }
    cout << sb.substr(ans.second - 1, ans.first) << '\n';

return 0;
}

    }

    if(ai == -1) {

        }
        else {
            r = m - 1;
        }
    }
    return ans;
}
 
int compare(Hashing& ha, Hashing& hb, int i, int j, int x, int y) {
    int lc = lcp(ha, hb, i, j, x, y);
    int l1 = (j - i + 1), l2 = (y - x + 1);
    if(lc == l1 or lc == l2) {
        if(l1 == l2) return 0;
        if(l1 < l2) return 1;
        if(l1 > l2) return -1;
    }
    if(ha.s[i + lc - 1] < hb.s[x + lc - 1]) return 1;
    else return -1;
}

    s = s + s;
    Hashing hs(s);
    int min_start = 0;
    for(int i = 1; i < n; i++) {
        if(compare(hs, hs, i + 1, i + n, min_start + 1, min_start + n)  >= 0) {
            min_start = i;
        }
    }
    cout << s.substr(min_start, n) << '\n';
    
return 0;
}

    ip2 = modpow(p2, MOD2 - 2, MOD2);
    ipw[0] = {1, 1};
    for(int i = 1; i < N; i++) {
        ipw[i].first = 1LL * ipw[i - 1].first * ip1 % MOD1;
        ipw[i].second = 1LL * ipw[i - 1].second * ip2 % MOD2;
    }
}
struct Hashing {
    int n;
    string s;
    vector<pair<int, int>> hs;
    Hashing() {}
    Hashing(string _s) {
        n = _s.size();
        s = _s;
        hs.emplace_back(0, 0);
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            pair<int, int> p;
            p.first = (hs[i].first + 1LL * pw[i].first * s[i] % MOD1) % MOD1;
            p.second = (hs[i].second + 1LL * pw[i].second * s[i] % MOD2) % MOD2;
            hs.push_back(p);
        }
    }
    pair<int, int> get_hash(int l, int r) {
        assert(1 <= l && l <= r && r <= n);
        pair<int, int> ans;
        ans.first = (hs[r].first - hs[l - 1].first + MOD1) * 1LL * ipw[l - 1].first % MOD1;
        ans.second = (hs[r].second - hs[l - 1].second + MOD2) * 1LL * ipw[l - 1].second % MOD2;
        return ans;
    }
    pair<int, int> get_hash() {
        return get_hash(1, n);
    }
};


int32_t main() {
    ios_base::sync_with_stdio(false); cin.tie(NULL);
    prec();
    
    string a, b;
    cin >> a >> b;
    int sza = (int) a.size(), szb = (int) b.size();
    Hashing ha(a), hb(b + b);
    set<pair<int, int>> shifts;
    for(int i = 0; i < szb; i++) {
        shifts.insert(hb.get_hash(i + 1, i + szb));
    }
    int ans = 0;
    for(int i = 0; i + szb - 1 < sza; i++) {
        if(shifts.count(ha.get_hash(i + 1, i + szb))) ans++;
    }
    cout << ans << '\n';

return 0;
}

CSES 2420: Palindromic Queries

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;
 
const int N = 2e5 + 9;
pair<int, int> a[N];
 
int modpow(long long a, long long n, const int m) {
    int r = 1 % m;
    a %= m;
    if(n < 0) a += m;
    while (n) {
        if(n & 1) r = (long long) r * a % m;
        a = (long long) a * a % m;
        n >>= 1;
    }
    return r;
}
 
const int MOD1 = 127657753, MOD2 = 987654319;
const int p1 = 137, p2 = 277;
int ip1, ip2;
pair<int, int> pw[N], ipw[N];
void prec() {
    pw[0] = {1, 1};
    for(int i = 1; i < N; i++) {
        pw[i].first = 1LL * pw[i - 1].first * p1 % MOD1;
        pw[i].second = 1LL * pw[i - 1].second * p2 % MOD2;
    }
    ip1 = modpow(p1, MOD1 - 2, MOD1);
    ip2 = modpow(p2, MOD2 - 2, MOD2);
    ipw[0] = {1, 1};
    for(int i = 1; i < N; i++) {
        ipw[i].first = 1LL * ipw[i - 1].first * ip1 % MOD1;
        ipw[i].second = 1LL * ipw[i - 1].second * ip2 % MOD2;
    }
}
struct Hashing {
    int n;
    string s;
    vector<pair<int, int>> hs;
    Hashing() {}
    Hashing(string _s) {
        n = _s.size();
        s = _s;
        hs.emplace_back(0, 0);
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            pair<int, int> p;
            p.first = (hs[i].first + 1LL * pw[i].first * s[i] % MOD1) % MOD1;
            p.second = (hs[i].second + 1LL * pw[i].second * s[i] % MOD2) % MOD2;
            hs.push_back(p);
        }
    }
};
 
struct ST {
    #define lc (n << 1)
    #define rc ((n << 1) + 1)
    pair<int, int> t[4 * N];
    static const int inf = 1e9;
    ST() {
        memset(t, 0, sizeof t);
    }
    inline void pull(int n) {
        t[n].first = (t[lc].first + t[rc].first) % MOD1;  
        t[n].second = (t[lc].second + t[rc].second) % MOD2;  
    }
    inline pair<int, int> combine(pair<int, int> a, pair<int, int> b) {
        return {(a.first + b.first) % MOD1, (a.second + b.second) % MOD2};
    }
    void build(int n, int b, int e) {
        if(b == e) {
            t[n] = a[b];
            return;
        }
        int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
        build(lc, b, mid);
        build(rc, mid + 1, e);
        pull(n);
    }
    void upd(int n, int b, int e, int i, pair<int, int> x) {
        if(b > i || e < i) return;
        if(b == e && b == i) {
            t[n] = x;
            return;
        }
        int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
        upd(lc, b, mid, i, x);
        upd(rc, mid + 1, e, i, x);
        pull(n);
    }
    pair<int, int> query(int n, int b, int e, int i, int j) {
        if(b > j || e < i) return {0, 0};
        if(b >= i && e <= j) return t[n];
        int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
        return combine(query(lc, b, mid, i, j), query(rc, mid + 1, e, i, j));
    }
}t1, t2;
 
pair<int, int> sub_hash(pair<int, int> hash, int x) {
    return {1LL * hash.first * ipw[x - 1].first % MOD1, 1LL * hash.second * ipw[x - 1].second % MOD2};
}
 
int32_t main() {
    ios_base::sync_with_stdio(false); cin.tie(NULL);
    prec();
    int n , m;
    cin >> n >> m;
    string s;
    cin >> s;
    for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        a[i + 1].first = (1LL * s[i] * pw[i].first) % MOD1;
        a[i + 1].second = (1LL * s[i] * pw[i].second) % MOD2;
    }
    t1.build(1, 1, n);
 
    string rs = s;
    reverse(rs.begin(), rs.end());
    for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        a[i + 1].first = (1LL * rs[i] * pw[i].first) % MOD1;
        a[i + 1].second = (1LL * rs[i] * pw[i].second) % MOD2;
    }
    t2.build(1, 1, n);
 
    while(m--) {
        int k; cin >> k;
        if(k == 1) {
            int x; char c;
            cin >> x >> c;
            pair<int, int> v = {(1LL * c * pw[x - 1].first) % MOD1, (1LL * c * pw[x - 1].second) % MOD2};
            t1.upd(1, 1, n, x, v);
            v = {(1LL * c * pw[n - x].first) % MOD1, (1LL * c * pw[n - x].second) % MOD2};
            t2.upd(1, 1, n, n - x + 1, v);
        }
        else {
            int x, y;
            cin >> x >> y;
            auto hash1 = t1.query(1, 1, n, x, y);
            auto hash2 = t2.query(1, 1, n, n - y + 1, n - x + 1);
 
            if(sub_hash(hash1, x) == sub_hash(hash2, n - y + 1)) {
                cout << "YES" << '\n';
            }
            else {
                cout << "NO" << '\n';
            }
        }
    }
 
return 0;
}

CSES 1111: Longest Palindrome

Editorial: N/A

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;
 
const int N = 1e6 + 9;
 
int modpow(long long a, long long n, const int m) {
    int r = 1 % m;
    a %= m;
    if(n < 0) a += m;
    while (n) {
        if(n & 1) r = (long long) r * a % m;
        a = (long long) a * a % m;
        n >>= 1;
    }
    return r;
}
 
const int MOD1 = 127657753, MOD2 = 987654319;
const int p1 = 137, p2 = 277;
int ip1, ip2;
pair<int, int> pw[N], ipw[N];
void prec() {
    pw[0] = {1, 1};
    for(int i = 1; i < N; i++) {
        pw[i].first = 1LL * pw[i - 1].first * p1 % MOD1;
        pw[i].second = 1LL * pw[i - 1].second * p2 % MOD2;
    }
    ip1 = modpow(p1, MOD1 - 2, MOD1);
    ip2 = modpow(p2, MOD2 - 2, MOD2);
    ipw[0] = {1, 1};
    for(int i = 1; i < N; i++) {
        ipw[i].first = 1LL * ipw[i - 1].first * ip1 % MOD1;
        ipw[i].second = 1LL * ipw[i - 1].second * ip2 % MOD2;
    }
}
struct Hashing {
    int n;
    string s;
    vector<pair<int, int>> hs;
    Hashing() {}
    Hashing(string _s) {
        n = _s.size();
        s = _s;
        hs.emplace_back(0, 0);
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            pair<int, int> p;
            p.first = (hs[i].first + 1LL * pw[i].first * s[i] % MOD1) % MOD1;
            p.second = (hs[i].second + 1LL * pw[i].second * s[i] % MOD2) % MOD2;
            hs.push_back(p);
        }
    }
    pair<int, int> get_hash(int l, int r) {
        assert(1 <= l && l <= r && r <= n);
        pair<int, int> ans;
        ans.first = (hs[r].first - hs[l - 1].first + MOD1) * 1LL * ipw[l - 1].first % MOD1;
        ans.second = (hs[r].second - hs[l - 1].second + MOD2) * 1LL * ipw[l - 1].second % MOD2;
        return ans;
    }
    pair<int, int> get_hash() {
        return get_hash(1, n);
    }
};
 
bool ache(Hashing& ha, Hashing& hb, int l) {
    for(int i = 1; i + l - 1 <= ha.n; i++) {
        int j = i + l - 1;
        if(ha.get_hash(i, j) == hb.get_hash(ha.n - j + 1, ha.n - i + 1)) return true;
    }
    return false;
}
 
int32_t main() {
    ios_base::sync_with_stdio(false); cin.tie(NULL);
    prec();
    string s;
    cin >> s;
    string rs = s;
    reverse(rs.begin(), rs.end());
    Hashing hs(s), hrs(rs);
 
    int l = 1, r = (s.size() + 1) / 2;
    int ans1 = 1;
    while(l <= r) {
        int m = l + r >> 1;
        if(ache(hs, hrs, 2 * m - 1)) {
            ans1 = m;
            l = m + 1;
        }
        else {
            r = m - 1;
        }
    }
 
    l = 1, r = s.size() / 2;
    int ans2 = 0;
    while(l <= r) {
        int m = l + r >> 1;
        if(ache(hs, hrs, 2 * m)) {
            ans2 = m;
            l = m + 1;
        }
        else {
            r = m - 1;
        }
    }
    int ans = max(2 * ans1 - 1, 2 * ans2);
    for(int i = 1; i + ans - 1 <= (int)s.size(); i++) {
        int j  = i + ans - 1;
        if(hs.get_hash(i, j) == hrs.get_hash(hrs.n - j + 1, hrs.n - i + 1)) {
            cout << s.substr(i - 1, ans) << '\n';
            break;
        }
    }
return 0;
}

ACMP 1157: Sub-Palindromes

Editorial: N/A

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

const int N = 2e5 + 9;

int modpow(long long a, long long n, const int m) {
    int r = 1 % m;
    a %= m;
    if(n < 0) a += m;
    while (n) {
        if(n & 1) r = (long long) r * a % m;
        a = (long long) a * a % m;
        n >>= 1;
    }
    return r;
}

const int MOD1 = 127657753, MOD2 = 987654319;
const int p1 = 137, p2 = 277;
int ip1, ip2;
pair<int, int> pw[N], ipw[N];
void prec() {
    pw[0] = {1, 1};
    for(int i = 1; i < N; i++) {
        pw[i].first = 1LL * pw[i - 1].first * p1 % MOD1;
        pw[i].second = 1LL * pw[i - 1].second * p2 % MOD2;
    }
    ip1 = modpow(p1, MOD1 - 2, MOD1);
    ip2 = modpow(p2, MOD2 - 2, MOD2);
    ipw[0] = {1, 1};
    for(int i = 1; i < N; i++) {
        ipw[i].first = 1LL * ipw[i - 1].first * ip1 % MOD1;
        ipw[i].second = 1LL * ipw[i - 1].second * ip2 % MOD2;
    }
}
struct Hashing {
    int n;
    string s;
    vector<pair<int, int>> hs;
    Hashing() {}
    Hashing(string _s) {
        n = _s.size();
        s = _s;
        hs.emplace_back(0, 0);
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            pair<int, int> p;
            p.first = (hs[i].first + 1LL * pw[i].first * s[i] % MOD1) % MOD1;
            p.second = (hs[i].second + 1LL * pw[i].second * s[i] % MOD2) % MOD2;
            hs.push_back(p);
        }
    }
    pair<int, int> get_hash(int l, int r) {
        assert(1 <= l && l <= r && r <= n);
        pair<int, int> ans;
        ans.first = (hs[r].first - hs[l - 1].first + MOD1) * 1LL * ipw[l - 1].first % MOD1;
        ans.second = (hs[r].second - hs[l - 1].second + MOD2) * 1LL * ipw[l - 1].second % MOD2;
        return ans;
    }
    pair<int, int> get_hash() {
        return get_hash(1, n);
    }
} hs, hrs;

bool ispal(int l, int r) {
    l += 1, r += 1;
    return hs.get_hash(l, r) == hrs.get_hash(hs.n - r + 1, hs.n - l + 1);
}

bool odd_okay(int c, int l) {
    return ispal(c - l, c + l);
}

bool even_okay(int c, int l) {
    return ispal(c - l, c + l + 1);
}

int32_t main() {
    ios_base::sync_with_stdio(false); cin.tie(NULL);
    prec();
    
    string s;
    cin >> s;
    int n = (int) s.size();
    hs = Hashing(s);
    reverse(s.begin(), s.end());
    hrs = Hashing(s);
    long long total = 0;
    // checking for odd palindrome
    for(int c = 0; c < n; c++) {
        int l = 0, r = min(c, n - c - 1);
        int ans = -1;
        while(l <= r) {
            int m = l + r >> 1;
            if(odd_okay(c, m)) {
                ans = m;
                l = m + 1;
            }
            else {
                r = m - 1;
            }
        }
        total += ans + 1;
    }
    // Checking for even palidrome
    for(int c = 0; c < n - 1; c++) {
        int l = 0, r = min(c, n - c - 2);
        int ans = -1;
        while(l <= r) {
            int m = l + r >> 1;
            if(even_okay(c, m)) {
                ans = m;
                l = m + 1;
            }
            else {
                r = m - 1;
            }
        }
        total += ans + 1;
    }
    cout << total << '\n';

return 0;
}
